snippet.title: Swim-Inspired Kids Exercise (Advanced: Superhero Adventure) | Goldfish At Home
snippet.description:
Welcome to Goldfish at Home! We’ve created a series of fun and interactive at-home exercises for kids inspired by the swim skills we teach during lessons at Goldfish.

This video is all about the Butterfly stroke! Join as Miss Jenny and her friend Jack demonstrate techniques and exercises that will help make your super swimmer stronger and more efficient in the pool.

Don’t forget, if you want to review earlier skills, feel free to watch the previous level videos!

Love Goldfish At Home? 

Be sure to subscribe and hit the bell to receive post notifications! That way, you’ll never miss an opportunity to dive into our next at-home adventure. 

Check out our other at-home exercise activities for kids here:

Ocean Life Adventure: https://bit.ly/2XA2daX

Nature Adventure: https://bit.ly/2Yi0qHK 

Water Safety Adventure: https://bit.ly/2Ypc7g3 

Visit our website for more at-home activities your kids will love: http://www.goldfishswimschool.com/activities

Don’t forget to share pictures of your family having fun with us on social media by using #GoldfishAtHome. 

Join our community of Goldfish families by connecting with us on:

Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/goldfishswimschool
Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/goldfishswimschool
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/goldfishswim 
Website: http://www.goldfishswimschool.com

About Goldfish Swim School:

Founded by husband and wife team Chris and Jenny McCuiston, Goldfish Swim School provides swim lessons and water safety instruction to infants and children ages four months to 12 years, and teaches more than 135,000 students per week how to swim and be safer in and around the water. Classes are offered by specially trained instructors in a safe, child-friendly and fun environment using Goldfish’s research-based philosophy called The Science of SwimPlay®. Goldfish Swim School is currently in the process of expanding franchise opportunities throughout North America, with more than 100 schools open, and an additional 100+ in development in more than 34 states and Canada.

snippet.description:
A fun and energetic home workout for children and adults using kettlebells

What is in this workout?
Warm-Up -  3 min
Workout Includes:
1. Round the world
2. Deadlift
3. Kettlebell Swing
4. Kettlebell Strict Press
5. Upright Row
6. Russian Twist
7. Squat

Round 1 = 15 sec work / 15 sec rest
Round 2 = 30 sec work / 15 sec rest
Round 3 = 45 sec work / 20 sec rest


Partner Exercise
1. Plank hand tap
2. Squat Hold
3. Leg Lowers
4. Partner Jump

Round 1 = 15 sec work / 15 sec rest
Round 2 = 30 sec work / 15 sec rest
Round 3 = 45 sec work / 20 sec rest

Give the workout a try and let us know how you got on

Dave, Sam & Eve

snippet.title: Calming Exercises for Kids: Breathing and Stretching
snippet.description:
The aim of this video is to help little people manage the big emotions they experience. It includes some simple breathing exercises and stretches to help kids release tension and calm down when they are feeling stressed, frustrated or anxious.

I suggest that you practice the exercises in this video with your child when they are feeling calm, engaged and ready to learn. When they are familiar with the video you can remind them of their breathing exercises/stretches at times they are experiencing stress and help them learn to calm themselves down.

When our little monkey has his mouth closed, he is breathing in. When his mouth is open, he is breathing out. During stretches, encourage your child to breath deeply and slowly.

As a parent, I know the importance of developing a healthy relationship with exercise from a young age! It's what lead to my career as a professional athlete! Which is why I am SO excited to share LEANSQUAD’s first ever KID's WORKOUT in preparation for the #BackToLean Schools Initiative starting next week, September 16th (https://lean-squad.com/blog/backtolean-2019)! 

My goal is to make health and fitness a part of EVERY family, and this workout is the perfect starting point for any parents, kids, students (or anyone for that matter) who is looking to become healthier, fitter and more active!!!

This workout is all body weight and you need no equipment. Likewise, it’s suitable for kids and adults of ALL ages, and is very low impact. Don’t let that fool you though, it is still 25 minutes of sweaty, lean fun!!! Similarly, you don’t need much space at all to get this done. The most important thing is that you just get it done! Taking the first step is often the hardest, but if you get this workout done, you will be well on your way to succeeding on your health and wellness journey. 

Likewise, it is important to remember, that you or your kids should go at your own pace! We are not competing against one another. All that matters is that we do OUR BEST!!! snippet.title: Letters of the Alphabet | Capital Letters | Uppercase Letters | Alphabet Workout | Jack Hartmann
snippet.description:
Alphabet Workout strengthens alphabet recognition, letter formation skills and fitness of your class.  My Alphabet Workout song - Upper Case follows the Zaner - Bloser instructions for writing the upper case letters to develop the exercise movements and verbal letter formation directions. 

This song incorporates visual, auditory and kinesthetic learning. Gross motor movements are used to form the letters to enhance physical activity. Children follow my movements as I form the upper case letters of the alphabet. 

The more we engage our children in movement, the more we really are strengthening their health and well-being. I made the letters as large as possible so your children can clearly see and watch me form the letters. 

Play this song every day to help your children get great practice forming the letters and making body and brain connections.

Brain and Body Builders DVD:
http://www.jackhartmann.com/brain-and-body-builders/

snippet.title: Fun Phonics Fitness Song | Letter Sounds for Kids | Exercise Song | Jack Hartmann
snippet.description:
This letter sound song is a fun way of exercising your body and your brain to the letter sounds.  Say the letters, the letter sound and a word that begins with each letter sound as you build your body and your brain by doing different exercises to each group of letter sounds and alphabet recognition.    We incorporate lots of cross body movements to build brain and body connections while building fitness and phonics skills.  This movement song for kids will encourage active and engaged learning while learning about letter sounds.  Fun Phonics Fitness Song.

snippet.title: Monsters In The Dark | Little Angel Kids Songs & Nursery Rhymes
snippet.description:
Nighttime can be a very scary time.  Monsters lurk in the shadows, and ghosts hide in the closet.  No need to be afraid Baby John, you aren’t afraid of the dark.   Enjoy this new version of the Monsters In The Dark and other exciting songs. #littleangel  #littleangelnurseryrhymes  #babyjohnsongs  #babyjohnnurseryrhymes

(🔔) Subscribe to Little Angel for new videos ►► http://bit.ly/Subscribe_to_LittleAngel 

List of Kids Songs;
00:04 I Don't Like Being Alone In The Dark
03:59 This is The Way I Get Dressed 
07:53 Be Safe! Wash Your Hands
11:12 Yes Yes Fruits Are Good For You
15:17 Exercise Song
18:55 No More Snacks Baby John

Song Lyrics 

Now we are alone,
All alone in the dark
What’s that shadow? What could it be? 
It looks like a monster to me

Let’s check and see
Where is it coming from?
It must be a monster, I’m afraid
Phew! It was just in our heads

Once upon a time
there was a big/scary wolf 
howling so loud and its eyes so bright
No one came out at night.

Look it’s dark outside,
we’re alone in the dark.
What’s that noise, behind the door?
Now I can’t see anymore

Oh no, who’s there?
Do you see what I see?
It’s so creepy! I’m so scared
We hide all and then we all wait

There it was again
I need to go and check
Let’s be brave, let’s find out 
Phew, just a bush outside

Oh I am so scared
Let’s stay here and wait
No, no go, stay with us
it’s so scary out there

There it was again
What’s behind that door?
Just a toy car/ shining at night 
No need to be afraid

Something just moved!
It’s getting closer to us
it’s so scary, I’m so scared
I’m sure it’s not in my head

What was that noise?
Looks like a branch to me
It’s not a monster, just a tree
No need to be afraid
